{"TopicId":152716,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"What do YOU call Jool\u0027s innermost moon--you know, the one with the ocean?","CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:11:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:11:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn amusing little poll (or is it \u0022pol\u0022)? based on the most recent pages of \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/126293-kerbfleet-a-jool-odyssey-chapter-16-pg4-some-ominous-pronounce-ments/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=2867231\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbfleet: A Jool Odyssey\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nETA: and if you\u0027re wondering why there is no \u0022something else\u0022 option for Pol, it\u0027s because there ARE no other reasonable options. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T20:14:16Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 08:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kuzzter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:22:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480363872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nETA: and if you\u0027re wondering why there is no \u0022something else\u0022 option for Pol, it\u0027s because there ARE no other reasonable options. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pool\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:24:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480364554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pool\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWrong. \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E**BZZZZZZZZZTTTT!!**\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:25:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480364554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pool\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people are just determined to be unreasonable, I guess.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cydonian Monk","CreatedById":69224,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:30:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI should put an asterisk next to my votes and a footnote that reads \u0022Grew up in West Virginia surrounded by New Yorkers, New Jerseites,\u00A0and Pittsburghers and has lived in Tex-Mex-Loosianaland for more than a decade. May not know how to speak English properly.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:32:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480363872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nETA: and if you\u0027re wondering why there is no \u0022something else\u0022 option for Pol, it\u0027s because there ARE no other reasonable options. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pal\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:32:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIDK why, but I\u0027ve always pronounced Laythe with the first and second syllable rhyming:\u00A0Lay-thay\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:34:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480365150\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295210\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022monstah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, monstah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pal\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah \u0022buddy\u0022, I like you too. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0111narwhalz","CreatedById":110660,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:35:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of an old Scott Manley episode, pronouncing \u0022kethane\u0022 in interesting ways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeh-thane, key-thane, and (my favorite) keh-thahn-ee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:37:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480364641\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWrong. \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E**BZZZZZZZZZTTTT!!**\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#a9a9a9;\u0022\u003E*Deddly has gone into hibernation\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:46:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTool, Valentina, pollen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alchemist","CreatedById":8825,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:47:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480362634\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269224\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cydonian Monk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I see \u0022Laythe\u0022 in English, my brain attaches it to lathe, a mono-syllablic word. For\u00A0\u041B\u0430\u0439\u0442\u044D, on the otherhand,\u00A0\u0442\u044D is definitly its own syllable\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the thing - depending on what language I vocalize it in, the sounding is really different (on the other hand, even simple names like Kerbin get different syllables accentuated in different languages).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here\u0027s the peril of actually using 3 languages - when not specifically vocalizing the text in one particular language (and quick reading is one of the cases of converting words almost straight to meaning without emphasizing the sound) I often have different words in one thought in different languages (or with different accents)... And sometimes my accent gets briefly stuck somewhere in between.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AviosAdku","CreatedById":165040,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T20:54:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor me it was:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaythe: Lathe (the tool)\u003Cbr\u003E\nVall: Val (as in the shortened form of Valentina)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPol: Pollen\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDialect: Australian English\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:07:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTool, Val (hi Captin!), Poland\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The solid fuel chemist","CreatedById":158384,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:09:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntool, valentina, poland\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T21:10:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 09:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by The solid fuel chemist\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kunok","CreatedById":147982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:23:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not really sure if I pronounce correctly in english so better I explain myself. I say laite, val, pol, just as is spoken in Spanish, after all this is a game from mexico \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E the only doubt is that there isn\u0027t \u0022th\u0022 in spanish but supposedly you don\u0027t pronounce the \u0022h\u0022 anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomewhat oftopic, isn\u0027t there any writing normalization initiative in english linguists? Because I think is time... If you know one language you should be able to pronounce/write every word of them even if is the first time you read/hear it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cydonian Monk","CreatedById":69224,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:32:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480368218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147982\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kunok\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, kunok said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomewhat oftopic, isn\u0027t there any writing normalization initiative in english linguists?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGeorge Orwell was a large proponent of such back in the 40s, before he made a pretty quick about-face. (See: Basic English.) He\u00A0realized how terribly wrong such a project could go and wrote a rather nice book about it. And a doubleplusgood paper too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the fallout from both has poisoned the well of cleaning up English ever since.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T21:36:07Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 09:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Cydonian Monk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:45:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480368218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147982\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kunok\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, kunok said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomewhat oftopic, isn\u0027t there any writing normalization initiative in english linguists?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. We can\u0027t even decide among ourselves how things should be \u003Cem\u003Espelled \u003C/em\u003Elet alone pronounced. Some favour one spelling, while others favor another. And then we have the debates involving how things are spelled now as opposed to the way they \u003Cem\u003Eused \u003C/em\u003Eto be spelt. And if you understand \u003Cem\u003Ethat \u003C/em\u003Eall right, then consider the\u00A0innumerable alternate spellings that were once errors but, through frequent use, are now alright for all but the most formal situations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kunok","CreatedById":147982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:46:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480368755\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269224\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cydonian Monk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Cydonian Monk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGeorge Orwell was a large proponent of such back in the 40s, before he made a pretty quick about-face. (See: Basic English.) He\u00A0realized how terribly wrong such a project could go and wrote a rather nice book about it too.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot simplifying the language, it isn\u0027t the same. Just make a coherent pronunciation/writing, update the orthographic/pronunciation rules, most european languages did several times that, not changing even one word definition.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExamples \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_orthography_reform_of_1996\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_orthography_reform_of_1996 \u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480369539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. We can\u0027t even decide among ourselves how things should be \u003Cem\u003Espelled \u003C/em\u003Elet alone pronounced. Some favour one spelling, while others favor another. And then we have the debates involving how things are spelled now as opposed to the way they \u003Cem\u003Eused \u003C/em\u003Eto be spelt. And if you understand \u003Cem\u003Ethat \u003C/em\u003Eall right, then consider the\u00A0innumerable alternate spellings that were once errors but, through frequent use, are now alright for all but the most formal situations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat problem happened in every single language, someone should start. If portuguese speakers have been able to reunify the grammar why shouldn\u0027t be able english? Or do different dialects, but normalize it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T21:49:06Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 09:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kunok\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:46:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480365150\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295210\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022monstah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, monstah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pal\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480364554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Pool\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022P\u00E4\u00F6\u00E8l\u0022\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T21:46:42Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 09:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Matuchkin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:47:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m continental European, so I use flat, open vowels by default, in contrast to native English speakers. Especially when I\u0027ve never heard a word pronounced before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis makes my \u0022Vall\u0022 sport the same \u0022a\u0022 as in \u0022father\u0022, not the one in \u0022hall\u0022. But because it\u0027s a double L, it still is a bit alike the second option in the poll above - a short vowel followed by a strong consonant.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should be noted that Kerbals speak Spanish (if backwards), and Spanish definitely has a strong presence of flat, open vowels. So in my mind, this pronunciation is perfectly believable as something the Kerbals themselves would use. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alchemist","CreatedById":8825,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:47:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480365315\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110660\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00220111narwhalz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, 0111narwhalz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of an old Scott Manley episode, pronouncing \u0022kethane\u0022 in interesting ways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeh-thane, key-thane, and (my favorite) keh-thahn-ee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, that\u0027s definitely was supposed to be like \u003Cem\u003Emethane\u003C/em\u003E, just with \u003Cem\u003Ek\u003C/em\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t fix the problem of different pronunciation in different languages, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the \u041B\u0430\u0439\u0442\u044D variant, it sounds like \u003Cem\u003Elatte\u003C/em\u003E, just with first \u003Cem\u003Et\u003C/em\u003E replaced by \u003Cem\u003Ey\u003C/em\u003E, making the first syllable\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ELay-\u003C/em\u003E sound about like \u003Cem\u003Eli-\u003C/em\u003E in \u003Cem\u003Elight\u003C/em\u003E or \u003Cem\u003Elike\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWell, that\u0027s as good as I could explain it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut when I\u0027m saying Laythe in English it really sounds like \u003Cem\u003Elathe\u003C/em\u003E (even if I really wasn\u0027t familiar with this word in English until this discussion)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480369539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. We can\u0027t even decide among ourselves how things should be \u003Cem\u003Espelled \u003C/em\u003Elet alone pronounced. Some favour one spelling, while others favor another. And then we have the debates involving how things are spelled now as opposed to the way they \u003Cem\u003Eused \u003C/em\u003Eto be spelt. And if you understand \u003Cem\u003Ethat \u003C/em\u003Eall right, then consider the\u00A0innumerable alternate spellings that were once errors but, through frequent use, are now alright for all but the most formal situations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat post is a work of art.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:52:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480369657\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00228825\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alchemist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, Alchemist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, that\u0027s definitely was supposed to be like \u003Cem\u003Emethane\u003C/em\u003E, just with \u003Cem\u003Ek\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell yeah, but I\u0027ve heard professionals say both meh-thane and mee-thane. (That last one is just silly, sort of the way shoppers at a certain US big-box store put on airs and call it \u0022Targ\u00E9t\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure we English speakers have half a dozen different ways to pronounce \u0022See-Aitch-Four\u0022, if you want to get technical \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T22:15:19Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 10:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kuzzter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"greenTurtle1134","CreatedById":167701,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-28T21:55:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480369539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome favour one spelling, while others favor another. And then we have the debates involving how things are spelled now as opposed to the way they \u003Cem\u003Eused \u003C/em\u003Eto be spelt. And if you understand \u003Cem\u003Ethat \u003C/em\u003Eall right, then consider the\u00A0innumerable alternate spellings that were once errors but, through frequent use, are now alright for all but the most formal situations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I\u0027m talking about)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222867646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480369539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Efavour \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003Eone spelling, while others \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Efavor \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003Eanother. And then we have the debates involving how things are \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Espelled \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003Enow as opposed to the way they \u003Cem\u003Eused \u003C/em\u003Eto be \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Espelt\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E. And if you understand \u003Cem\u003Ethat \u003C/em\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eall right\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E, then consider the\u00A0innumerable alternate spellings that were once errors but, through frequent use, are now \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ealright\u003C/strong\u003E \u003C/u\u003Efor all but the most formal situations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...yeah, I see what you did there!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRepliked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(later)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdited to make it less long... in the original version, I used different quotes for each word. Eeughhh!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-28T21:57:14Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2016 09:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by greenTurtle1134\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ESee \u0026quot;(later)\u0026quot;\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}